Interface BagInterface<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedBag, ResizeableArrayBag
public interface BagInterface<T>
This is the BagInterface interface which defines the Union, Intersection, and Difference methods.
Version:
1.2
Author:
George Matta, Pierlorenzo Peruzzo

    • toArray

      T[] toArray()
      Retrieves all entries that are in this bag.
      Returns:
      A newly allocated array of all the entries in the bag. Note: If the bag is empty, the returned array is empty.

    • union

      BagInterface<T> union(BagInterface<T> other)
      Finds the Union of two bags (T). A union is a collection which consists of all of the contents of the two collections that make it up.
      Parameters:
      other - The bag we are adding on to this bag.
      Returns:
      A new bag (T) object of the two bags unionized.

    • intersection

      BagInterface<T> intersection(BagInterface<T> other)
      Finds the Intersection of two bags (T). An intersection is a collection which consists of the items that exist in both bags that make it up.
      Parameters:
      other - The bag we are intersecting with this bag.
      Returns:
      A new bag (T) object of the two bags' intersection.

    • difference

      BagInterface<T> difference(BagInterface<T> other)
      Finds the Difference of two bags (T). A difference is a collection which consists of the items that exist in this bag but not the other bag.
      Parameters:
      other - The bag we are subtracting from this bag.
      Returns:
      A new bag (T) object of the two bags' difference.
